modules.description: Returns the current time as a float representing seconds since the Unix epoch. Accepts a timezone offset in seconds to adjust the result. Used to generate timestamps for logging or event tracking in distributed systems.

Returns the number of nanoseconds since the Unix epoch and a counter that starts at program initialization, useful for high-resolution timing and benchmarking. Operates on 63-bit integers to represent large time values. Used to measure elapsed time in performance-critical code and to generate unique, incrementing timestamps.
